{
  "doc_id": "29569",
  "text": "The occurrence of atrial fibrillation (AF), post cardiac surgery, was reported in five of the RCTs (total n = 488) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The results of the meta-analysis revealed a significant reduction in AF in patients with tight glycaemic control during surgery (OR = 0.76, 95% CI 0.58-0.99, p = 0.05, Z = 2.00, heterogeneity I 2 = 55%, p = 0.07) (Figure 3 ).",
